{
  "texts": [
    "Notably, Qwen2-VL, which employs a native vision encoder trained directly with the language model rather than pretraining on image modality first and then aligning to language modality, shows no performance loss and even improvement after modality projection, suggesting the potential of unified architectures.",
    "sual features, aligned features, and language embeddings.",
    "We observe that the distribution of the aligned features is similar to that of image features, meaning that the multimodal process preserves the visual semantics for some extent.",
    "Ideally, the aligned features should closely resemble the language embeddings.",
    "However, our observation reveals a significant disparity between the aligned feature space and the language embedding space, suggesting a lack of adequate modality alignment."
  ]
}